e same dynamic access sites? I believe they will since safeLoad and reflection with m.invoke should still work. However, it'll be with one class instead of several. I should consider how that change might affect the overall execution and effectiveness of the tests. It's a bit tricky!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_wOttSw9R8UrfAbWckyO4VfjG|fc_0cd2afb14a04b5a30169f7030c3a5881a18582f710388a9839", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/jakarta.xml.bind/jakarta.xml.bind-api/4.1.0-M1/src/test/java/jakarta_xml_bind/jakarta_xml_bind_api/support/WrongTypeContextFactory.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3514, "output": 1584, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27114, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777795831598, "responseId": "resp_0cd2afb14a04b5a30169f702f81cac81a191c8df65e5518f2b"}}
